## <a id="reqs"></a>Requirements

To use Azuqua with Pivotal Cloud Foundry, you’ll need the following:

* An Azuqua account (Public Cloud) with an Organization to design workflows. You can create your own account or an administrator can create one for you. For more information about managing users in an existing Organization, refer to [Manage Organizations](http://help.azuqua.com/help/manage-organizations) 

* An installation of Pivotal Cloud Foundry Elastic Runtime with UAA

* PCF Stemcell Ubuntu Trusty version 3261.12

* SSL certificates in your UAA that will validate successfully in the stemcell you deploy the Azuqua tile on

* Network ingress from and egress to Azuqua from the space where the tile is deployed and from users’ workstations

## <a id="limitations"></a>Limitations

The v0.9 Azuqua PCF tile is limited to providing Single Sign-On to a single Azuqua user.  All PCF users with UAA permissions to the deployed service will authenticate to Azuqua as the configured user.

